  <!-- S7 TIERS — verdict cards + matrix in DOM -->
  <section id="tiers">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">How Do the Breeder Types Compare Side by Side?</h2>
    <a class="inf" href="/african-grey-comparison/"><img class="sec-img inf-img" src="/african-grey-breeder-types-documentation-matrix.webp" srcset="/african-grey-breeder-types-documentation-matrix-760.webp 760w, /african-grey-breeder-types-documentation-matrix.webp 1408w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 760px" width="1408" height="768" alt="Documentation matrix comparing direct breeder, classified site, marketplace and rescue across USDA licence, CITES, DNA and PCR screening" loading="lazy"></a>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">Reading the Comparison Table</h3>
    <p>Same six documents, four channels, one honest read on each. The cards below are the fast version; the audited breeder-by-breeder table further down is the detailed one search engines pull from.</p>
    <div class="tier-grid">
      {tiers.map((t) => (
        <div class={t.win ? "tier-c win" : "tier-c"}>
          <div class="tier-head"><span class="tier-name">{t.name}</span><span class="tier-verdict">{t.verdict}</span></div>
          <ul class="tier-docs">
            {t.docs.map((d) => (<li><span class={`mk ${d[0]}`}>{d[0] === "y" ? "✓" : d[0] === "n" ? "✗" : "~"}</span>{d[1]}</li>))}
          </ul>
          <div class="tier-strip">{t.strip}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <h4 class="cag-h4">Why Documentation Is the Axis That Matters</h4>
    <p>You cannot judge a breeder on how tidy the aviary looks in a photo. You can judge one on whether a USDA number checks out, whether the CITES paperwork names the bird in front of you, and whether the PCR result has a lab on it.</p>
    <h5 class="cag-h5">What the Table Does Not Measure</h5>
    <p>Warmth, patience, the willingness to answer a nervous first-time owner's fifth email — none of it fits in a grid, and all of it matters. The documentation is the floor a breeder has to clear before any of the softer virtues count.</p>
    <h6 class="cag-h6">Breeder note: a nice facility is not verification</h6>
    <p>We have seen buyers reassured by a spotless aviary photo that turned out to be a stock image. A clean room is easy to fake; a verifiable license number and a per-bird PCR result are not.</p>
  </section>

